30/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A round table on possible changes to the law on local elections and the law on presidential elections was held in Skopje on Tuesday (29 June). Experts, legislators, law professors, government representatives and NGO representatives participated in the debate.
In other news, President Branko Crvenkovski returned from the NATO summit in Istanbul on Tuesday saying Macedonia hopes to receive an invitation to join the Alliance in 2006 and become a full-fledged member in 2007. He added that all meetings he attended suggested a growing consensus among NATO members in favour of accession by the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia. (Makfax, A1 TV, Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 30/06/04; A1 TV - 29/06/04)
